{
  "stem": "19807.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, in Bulgaria right now, the highest peak of the mountain is called Musala, which means the mountain of Musa, which is the prophet Moses, and that was next to heaven, which is Allah.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it still has that name, Musala.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they-- he would call him Musa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father was educated in Turkey.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And to talk about Bulgaria, you have to talk a bit about Turkey.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'm sure you know, Cydney, that the Jews of Spain were expelled in 1492.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the sultan, I believe it was [INAUDIBLE], sent his flotilla to Europe, to pick up the remnants of the Jews, that they're languishing on the shores of Italy, France, Europe, all over, and brought into Turkey.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if you follow history, you will see that Ottoman Empire benefit greatly by their industriousness.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And also, the Jews enjoyed freedom, enjoyed very good conditions, and they were able to immediately found their own schools.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they-- they-- they had schools for rabbis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- and in fact, if you go a little inland after that, you see that one of the most important religious-- religious books that was written by Rabbi Karo, was written in Bulgaria in the 16th century in the city of Nikopol.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Not to divert myself so much from my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a very strong, handsome man, and very enterprising.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even though he had to leave properties and everything, sort of, to leave in a hurry and to come back to Plovdiv, he had extreme pride in him.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He did not want the-- my uncles on my mother's side to situate him or to find him a job.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he found a job on his own.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he became a representative, like a sales executive, for a very large company.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
